# Architecture and dependencies

## Layers (strict)

- **UI (`src/finanmind/ui/`)**: presentation only. No business rules, no CSV/file I/O. Calls services.
- **Services (`src/finanmind/services/`)**: business logic only. Uses repositories for persistence. No direct CSV parsing in UI-facing helpers mixed with widgets.
- **Repositories (`src/finanmind/repositories/`)**: CSV (de)serialization and paths only. No budgeting/debt/investment rules.

Do not import UI from services or repositories. Prefer dependency direction: `ui → services → repositories`; **models** are shared DTOs/types only (no layer mixing).

## Single responsibility

- One domain per cohesive unit (e.g. budget vs debts vs income): separate modules/classes; no cross-domain logic in the wrong module.
- Prefer simplicity over frameworks.

## Dependencies

- Any third-party import → add an explicit pin or minimum version in `requirements.txt` (nothing used in code may be missing there).
- Standard library only does not need to be listed.
